  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (09d53c2 2022-03-31T00:36:36.371915+00:00)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nforge build\n\n### Operating System\n\nmacOS (amd)\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nWe found that deploying with CREATE2 gives us different addresses between environments. We tracked this down to the `ast` key in the artifacts. The devs in the support forum said that the metadata hash is included as part of the bytecode and is currently not configurable. We would like the ability to turn off the metadata appending to the bytecode. \r\n\r\nReference config by Uniswap to allow determinism: https://github.com/Uniswap/v3-core/blob/ed88be38ab2032d82bf10ac6f8d03aa631889d48/hardhat.config.ts#L57-L62",
